Description: Fix GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8 path-traversal in attachments + baggage replica updates
 Fixes two related issues in the langsmith Python SDK tracing path:
 .
 1) Three duplicated (tuple, Path) attachment-filesystem guards in
    create_run / update_run / multipart_ingest were broken: they only
    matched the (tuple, Path) shape, letting JSON-serialised list/str
    forms (e.g. ["text/plain", "/etc/passwd"]) bypass the check and be
    opened by the multipart serializer. Replace the three inline guards
    with a single fail-closed helper (_reject_filesystem_attachments)
    keyed off the data type via _attachment_references_filesystem.
 .
 2) Header-supplied baggage replica `updates` payloads were merged into
    the run without filtering, letting clients smuggle arbitrary fields
    (attachments, inputs, environment, ...) onto another run. Restrict
    `updates` from baggage replicas to a fail-closed allow-list
    (default: reroot, metadata, tags), configurable via the
    LANGSMITH_BAGGAGE_ALLOWED_UPDATE_FIELDS env var. The upstream commit
    introduced _filter_replica_for_headers as the single funnel for the
    dict path; that helper does not exist in 0.4.28, so for this backport
    _sanitize_header_updates is INLINED at the two replica-parse sites
    (legacy [project_name, updates] tuple/list form, and dict form).
 .
 Carries the matching unit-test additions for client.py and run_trees.py.
 Drops test_replica_endpoints.py additions because the upstream test
 file imports _Baggage / ServiceAuth / _extract_replica_auth which are
 not present in 0.4.28.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/langchain-ai/langsmith-sdk/commit/9c5515620f9bfa2145fc65d6f4353c4c8a3e96b6
 upstream, https://github.com/langchain-ai/langsmith-sdk/commit/93f19f317dd37a91d67b662b77691f980e5c56ed
Author: langchain-ai
Last-Update: 2026-06-29

